SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1259
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to congratulate the members of Team Leroy of
Greeneville on winning the Tennessee State
USBC Open.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those bowlers who,
through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of whom
we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of bowlers is Team Leroy of Greeneville, whose
members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of competitors and truly worthy of
admiration by winning the Tennessee State USBC Open; and
WHEREAS, named in honor of their longtime friend, Leroy Key, who passed away in
August 2025, Team Leroy, comprised of Clifford Doughty, David Painter, Mike Swatzell, Johnny
Painter, and Leroy Key's son, Cameron Key, dedicated this season to their namesake, who was
the heart and soul of their team; and
WHEREAS, taking to the lanes of the Smyrna Bowling Center, Team Leroy tallied a
team score of 3,430, ranking them first out of 475 teams in the team handicap event; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud Team Leroy for their outstanding success on the lanes; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we congratulate Team Leroy of Greeneville on
winning the Tennessee State USBC Open and extend to them our best wishes for every
continued success in bowling and in life.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
